cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper is about natural language processing and the use of categorical quantum mechanics to model the meaning of language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses empirical methods for comparing meanings, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of density matrices and commutative classical structures suggests a connection to linear algebra and data structures (cs.DS), while the discussion of iteration and ambiguity suggests a connection to semantics and information theory (cs.SI).
